Response: Just a curiosity: All researchers put an estimate time for competing a survey. Being a person who is doing this daily, I find it curious that the estimate time posted is never accurate. It is always taking more time than specified to complete a study. I do understand that a researcher is paying participants based on specified time. It is just not fare, because is our time invested in taking part in this, and we often do based on the estimated time.
(feedback)I thought I'd solved it then it got harder
